Class StmtVarDecl

  • java.lang.Object
    • sketch.compiler.ast.core.FENode
      • sketch.compiler.ast.core.stmts.Statement
        • sketch.compiler.ast.core.stmts.StmtVarDecl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<StmtVarDecl.VarDeclEntry>

    public class StmtVarDecl
extends Statement
implements java.lang.Iterable<StmtVarDecl.VarDeclEntry>
    A variable-declaration statement. This statement declares a sequence of variables, each of which has a name, a type, and an optional initialization value.
    Version:
    $Id$
    Author:
    David Maze <dmaze@cag.lcs.mit.edu>

    • Constructor Detail

      • StmtVarDecl

        public StmtVarDecl(FENode context,
                   java.util.List<? extends Type> types,
                   java.util.List<java.lang.String> names,
                   java.util.List<? extends Expression> inits)
        Create a new variable declaration with corresponding lists of types, names, and initialization values. The three lists passed in are duplicated, and may be mutated after calling this constructor without changing the value of this object. The types and names must all be non-null; if a particular variable is uninitialized, the corresponding initializer value may be null.
        Parameters:
        context - Context indicating what line and file this statement is created at
        types - List of Type of the variables declared here
        names - List of String of the names of the variables declared here
        inits - List of Expression (or null) containing initializers of the variables declared here
